                <div class="comment-body">
                    <p><cite data-comment-id="2241050">@<a class="user user-normal" href="http://dev.bukkit.org/bukkit-plugins/realmotd/?comment=111" title="View text">EddieFriday</a>: <a class="go-link" href="http://dev.bukkit.org/bukkit-plugins/realmotd/?comment=111" title="View text">Go</a></cite></p>
<p>RealMotd currently only displays MOTD when player joins game, but I'll add this feature as it's really quick <span class="emote emote-smile" title="Smile">:)</span></p>
<p>Configuration:
1. Set up your motd.mode in config file (plugins/RealMotd/config.yml) to Single
2. Set "motd.world-specific" to true in config file.
3. Now create file plugins/RealMotd/messages/world1/motd.txt   (this is MOTD for world1)
4. Create file plugins/RealMotd/messages/world2/motd.txt     (this is MOTD for world2)</p>

                </div>
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
            
        </div>
    </li>
                    
